The paper deals with the compressed membership problem for finite automata, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The use of straight-line programs (SLPs) to represent compressed transition labels suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.CC). The paper also employs techniques for encoding and decoding information, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
